Russian Equity Movers: AvtoVAZ, Lukoil and Raspadskaya in Moscow

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-03-18T16:23:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/russian-equity-movers-avtovaz-and-lukoil-are-active-in-moscow.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  added 0.6
percent to 1,747.32 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The gauge
advanced 1.6 percent this week. The dollar-denominated RTS Index
rallied 0.9 percent to 1,962.92 today.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO  AvtoVAZ (AVAZ)  , Russia’s largest carmaker, climbed
by its most since November, adding 8 percent to 30.424 rubles
after shareholder Troika Dialog said yesterday that  Japan ’s
Nissan Motor Co. is in talks about buying more than 25 percent
of the company.  OAO Lukoil (LKOH RX), Russia’s biggest oil producer, gained
for a third day, adding 1.5 percent to 2,015 rubles. Crude
advanced as much as 2.2 percent in  New York  after the United
Nations voted to ground  Libya  leader Muammar Qaddafi’s air force
amid escalating tension in the region. Oil fluctuated after
Libya said it agreed to a cease-fire.  OAO Raspadskaya (RASP RX) increased for a third day after
three people with knowledge of the matter said on March 15 that
OAO Mechel is considering acquiring shares in the Russian coal
producer. The stock climbed 3.4 percent to 201.75 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
